        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 11 at 6:20PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 620 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Abbeville. This storm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Abbeville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
